Description: Linux Bluetooth proximity lock for GNOME desktops
 BlueLatch watches one trusted Bluetooth phone over BlueZ D-Bus and locks the
 current desktop session when that phone is no longer nearby.
 .
 BlueLatch never auto-unlocks the machine. If the user manually unlocks while
 the trusted phone is still away, BlueLatch suppresses repeated re-locking
 until the phone returns and presence stabilizes again.
